  "text": "where m is a positive real number and x i and y i are two vectors in n-dimensional space. The Minkowski distance performs well when the dataset clusters are isolated or compacted; if the dataset does not fulfil this condition, then the large-scale attributes would dominate the others [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Another problem with Minkowski metrics is that the largest-scale feature dominates the rest. Thus, normalizing the continuous features is the solution to this problem [CITATION_3] .",
